Comment: 0,0:04:22.95,0:04:22.95,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:262956,262956}Part A
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.24,0:04:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:263248,265751}No matter what happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.75,0:04:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:265751,270339}it is unthinkable for a lady from my family\Nto marry some piano teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.33,0:04:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:270339,272591}I will never allow it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.92,0:04:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:272925,276678}Geneviève. You have\Nto remember about your pedigree.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.67,0:04:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:276678,278430}You know what I mean, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.01,0:04:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:282017,284061}Father. Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.06,0:04:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:284061,286772}It is two people fighting for their lives\Nwe're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.77,0:04:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:286772,288774}Now is not the time to lecture her\Nabout pedigree and whatnot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.77,0:04:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:288774,292277}We shall focus\Non stopping these two.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.15,0:04:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:293153,296073}Geneviève, I believe\Nyou do realize what you ought to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.74,0:04:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:296740,298116}Andréa…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.11,0:05:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:298116,301286}An excellent army officer\Nagainst a pianist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.28,0:05:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:301286,303413}You want neither\Nto lose their life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.45,0:05:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:304456,306333}Am I right, Geneviève?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.46,0:05:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:312464,315968}Ms. Isabelle, you have a guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.96,0:05:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:315968,318095}I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.68,0:05:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:324685,327354}Hey, Isabelle.\NHow have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.56,0:05:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:327562,329064}It's you again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.06,0:05:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:329064,332192}Yup. It's me, Jean Clément\Nwith my daily marriage proposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.90,0:05:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:332901,335279}I'm not in the mood\Nfor your jokes today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.27,0:05:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:335279,338865}Jean, do you even know\Nwhat's going on tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.86,0:05:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:338865,341827}Mr. Victor and Mr. Jules\Nwill fight in a duel, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.82,0:05:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:341827,344746}And three days from today,\Nyou're moving to Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.74,0:05:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:344746,347165}I know your schedule\Nlike the back of my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.16,0:05:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:347165,350002}You know all of this\Nand you still come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.00,0:05:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:350002,352504}What is wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.50,0:05:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:352504,357676}Especially in such a serious situation,\Nyou should be like me and try to have fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.26,0:06:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:359261,361805}I see. Try to have fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.93,0:06:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:361930,363849}Here. Such fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.97,0:06:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:365976,368603}I'm sick of you! Get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.31,0:06:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:370314,371982}Isabelle, I can't leave you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.85,0:06:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:372858,375694}It's true that I was weak\Nand a crybaby when we were kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.69,0:06:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:375694,377612}But I'm different now, Isabelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.61,0:06:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:377612,378697}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.69,0:06:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:378697,383702}Now I have the courage to pick up a rose\Nyou rejected and attach it to your chest!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.87,0:06:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:384870,386580}See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.87,0:06:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:389875,392961}"I have the courage to pick up a rose\Nyou rejected". She'll be head over heels!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.88,0:06:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:396882,399009}Stop strutting\Nlike the king of the roost.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.00,0:06:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:399009,401386}You're ten years too young\Nto hit on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.85,0:06:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:410854,412647}Nobody said it'd be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.12,0:07:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:433126,434169}Victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.79,0:07:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:434795,435629}Victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.71,0:07:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:436713,438840}I see you're as good as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.84,0:07:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:438840,442511}But you never know\Nwhat can happen in a duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.92,0:07:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:442928,444262}I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.26,0:07:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:444262,447516}I'm sorry on behalf of my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.51,0:07:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:447516,449726}But in the end,\Nit's only about some woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.72,0:07:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:449726,451937}It's not a matter\Nworth of a soldier's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.14,0:07:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:455148,458026}Soon this place will be swarming\Nwith the Prussian army.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.02,0:07:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:458026,460487}You're too important\Nfor the defense of Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.19,0:07:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:463198,465325}I don't want you to risk your life\Nover a mere woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.32,0:07:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:465325,466910}Andréa.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.91,0:07:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:466910,469204}I'm not taking part in this duel\Nfor a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.95,0:07:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:473959,475460}It's about pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.43,0:08:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:486430,488390}Your pride as a soldier?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.39,0:08:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:488390,492144}A high-ranking army officer, whose bride\Nwas stolen by an impoverished pianist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.43,0:08:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:492436,493979}This is who I am now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.97,0:08:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:493979,497065}Love is fickle.\NI'm fine with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.06,0:08:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:497065,500277}But how can I live as a soldier\Nwith a stain on his pride?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.11,0:08:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:501111,503488}If I can't protect\Neven my own pride,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.48,0:08:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:503488,506741}how can I protect the pride of France?\NHow can I defend Paris?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.24,0:08:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:510245,512122}I might be old-fashioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.12,0:08:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:512122,514291}But that's just who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.42,0:08:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:524426,528430}{\i1}Soon after a storm broke out,\Nunusual for this time of year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.43,0:08:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:528430,531349}{\i1}The city was bathed in a downpour,\Nthough it was only afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.34,0:08:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:531349,533727}{\i1}There was no one on the streets.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.72,0:08:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:533727,537230}{\i1}The only sound in Paris\Nwas heavy rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.23,0:09:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:537230,542068}{\i1}However, the Prussian army\Ndid not rest
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.06,0:09:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:542068,545071}{\i1}and mercilessly continued\Ntheir advance on Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.50,0:09:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:563507,565342}Jules, I heard everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.34,0:09:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:565342,566843}Stop this foolishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.84,0:09:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:566843,568053}Foolishness?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.05,0:09:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:568053,569721}You called it foolishness?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.72,0:09:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:569721,572349}I did. Your opponent\Nis a trained soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.34,0:09:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:572349,575602}You never drew a gun before.\NYou're no match for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.60,0:09:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:575602,578313}You're telling me to forfeit\Nand swallow the shame of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.31,0:09:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:578313,579856}Where's the shame in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.85,0:09:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:579856,581816}You have important\Nthings to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.81,0:09:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:581816,587364}Have you forgotten the words of the oath\Nwe made with the people in this cafe?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.61,0:09:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:587614,589658}Paris is our city!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.15,0:09:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:590158,591034}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.03,0:09:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:591034,593578}Who is going to\Ndefend our city? Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.57,0:09:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:593578,596289}The army? The politicians?\NThe aristocrats?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.28,0:09:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:596289,598333}No. It'll be us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.33,0:09:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:598333,599584}It'll be us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.58,0:10:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:599584,600919}We'll defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.91,0:10:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:600919,602546}We'll defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.54,0:10:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:602546,603838}Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.83,0:10:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:603838,605215}Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.84,0:10:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:610845,613265}You are one of those leaders.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.26,0:10:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:613265,617936}Don't give up your life\Nfor some rich chick you cannot have!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.48,0:10:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:620480,624401}Do you… Have you ever been\Nin love with someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.28,0:10:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:630282,633827}A man is willing to risk his life for a woman.\NI happen to love that woman as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.82,0:10:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:633827,638206}But I am going to love her\Nmore than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.96,0:10:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:642961,646965}I love Geneviève more than\NI value the life of that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.17,0:10:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:649175,652095}Let it go.\NTime heals wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.97,0:10:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:654973,656516}Don't die in vain!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.85,0:10:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:656850,658810}Die in vain?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.81,0:11:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:658810,661229}I love the city of Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.22,0:11:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:661229,662939}That is why\NI will fight to defend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.73,0:11:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:664733,666901}The same goes\Nfor the people I love.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.15,0:11:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:668153,669821}It is not in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.37,0:11:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:686379,687922}Victor is serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.92,0:11:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:687922,692218}The only chance to stop the duel\Nis to make Jules apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.63,0:11:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:692636,695305}If we don't stop them,\NJules is going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.30,0:11:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:695305,698183}Sister. Can't we do something?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.55,0:11:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:699559,701186}There is nothing I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.18,0:11:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:701186,703355}If the worst happens,\NI don't want to live anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.35,0:11:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:703355,704898}What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.39,0:11:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:706399,708652}Are you telling me…\Nto break up with Jules?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.98,0:11:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:710987,714032}Do you have any better idea\Nhow to save them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.20,0:11:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:716201,717202}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.20,0:11:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:717202,718203}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.20,0:11:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:718203,719829}Anything but that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.26,0:12:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:734260,739349}{\i1}Geneviève went\Nto Jules' apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.34,0:12:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:739349,742060}{\i1}She was about to say goodbye\Nfor the last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.64,0:12:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:745647,748608}{\i1}In order to stop the duel and\Nmake sure nobody dies,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.60,0:12:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:748608,753405}{\i1}Geneviève had no choice\Nbut to break up with Jules.
Comment: 0,0:12:41.83,0:12:41.83,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:761830,761830}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.17,0:12:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:777178,778847}Ms. Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.84,0:13:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:778847,780515}Thank you, Gaston.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.14,0:13:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:781141,783893}I can go back by myself.\NYou can go back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.89,0:13:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:783893,787355}All right.\NPlease be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.41,0:13:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:801411,802829}Geneviève!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.78,0:13:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:803788,805248}I came to say goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.70,0:13:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:807709,809502}Don't go to the duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.00,0:13:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:810003,812380}Just let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.96,0:13:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:812964,815800}I am going to marry Victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.25,0:13:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:816259,817677}Geneviève!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.67,0:13:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:818678,819804}Geneviève, don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.68,0:13:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:821681,826352}Until now, I've been running away from you,\Nusing your happiness as my excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.35,0:13:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:826352,829314}But that duel\Nactually opened my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.31,0:13:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:829314,831191}You shouldn't run away\Nfrom the ones you love.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.19,0:13:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:831191,833193}You shouldn't let go of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.19,0:13:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:833193,835528}You should stand up\Nand fight for them!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.36,0:13:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:837363,838531}Jules…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.07,0:14:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:845079,846748}Look around.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.33,0:14:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:854339,856341}That is our city.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.34,0:14:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:856341,859844}Filthy and cramped,\Nthis is our Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.84,0:14:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:859844,864182}This is where we grew up.\NThis is where we live.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.18,0:14:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:864182,866768}It is a completely different\Nworld to what you're used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.76,0:14:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:866768,869312}It's full of poverty and suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.43,0:14:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:869437,872190}Still, we're trying\Nour best to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.19,0:14:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:872190,873191}I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.35,0:14:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:873358,876069}But I'm begging you,\Ndon't go to that duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.27,0:14:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:876277,879322}That means to let you go.\NThis is something I cannot do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.32,0:14:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:879322,881032}I want you to live!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.40,0:14:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:882408,883368}I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.36,0:14:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:883368,885328}I don't want to die, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.57,0:14:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:885578,888081}But if it's for the things I love,\NI'm not afraid of dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.41,0:14:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:893419,895713}Jules…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.96,0:14:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:895964,898091}I don't want to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.88,0:15:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:901886,903930}It is time for you\Nto leave, Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.13,0:15:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:905139,909894}As long as the duel is not settled,\Nyou are not my woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.65,0:15:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:919654,920280}Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.61,0:15:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:921614,924200}Ms. Geneviève,\NI came to pick you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.65,0:15:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:924659,925994}Gaston…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.28,0:15:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:926286,929873}I am your loyal servant.\NI will always stand beside you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.16,0:15:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:935169,938256}{\i1}The duel that was about to take place\Ncould have only one outcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.25,0:15:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:938256,943303}{\i1}Both Jules and Geneviève\Nknew that all too well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.30,0:15:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:943303,948099}{\i1}Neither Jules or Geneviève\Nhad any hope for the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.35,0:15:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:952353,954647}{\i1}An old, worn out piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.64,0:15:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:954647,956983}{\i1}We've been through\Na lot together.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.98,0:15:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:956983,958943}{\i1}Today might be our last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.16,0:16:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:975168,979547}{\i1}Jules' piano continued\Nto ring until dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.04,0:16:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:980048,985386}{\i1}That night, nobody could sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.69,0:17:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1047699,1051327}Hey, Jules!\NAre you going, after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.72,0:17:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1068720,1071139}Why can't I go with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.13,0:17:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1071139,1074559}Duels between men are not something\Na young lady should watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.74,0:18:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1090742,1093995}{\i1}Isabelle felt uneasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.62,0:18:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1097623,1103212}{\i1}Isabelle had a longing for Victor\Nthat could only be described as being in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.39,0:18:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1114390,1116017}{\i1}Victor…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.01,0:18:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1116017,1120480}{\i1}Dear God, please protect Victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.02,0:18:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1125026,1127695}Jean? What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.69,0:18:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1127695,1129989}I arranged a horse\Nfor us in secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.98,0:18:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1129989,1133034}Isabelle, you're in love\Nwith Captain Langlois, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.70,0:18:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1134702,1136746}You can't go to see your crush,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.74,0:18:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1136746,1139248}but you have me,\Nyour childhood friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.24,0:19:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1139248,1143461}Let's go.\NI'll show you my rival's duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.46,0:19:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1143461,1144879}Jean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.83,0:19:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1145838,1147757}Come on, hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.03,0:19:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1175034,1177829}Nobody will see us from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.45,0:19:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1181457,1184168}I'll ask you this one last time.\NIs either of you willing to step down?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.25,0:19:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1185253,1188256}Captain Langlois, know that\NI have no grudge against you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.25,0:19:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1188256,1191926}But for Geneviève,\NI will fight you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.92,0:19:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1191926,1194262}A duel does not need words.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.47,0:20:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1199475,1202520}Both pistols have one bullet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.52,0:20:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1202520,1206190}I hope that no matter how this ends up,\Nthere will be no grudge.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.19,0:20:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1206190,1208901}Jules, you pick the pistol.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.23,0:20:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1210236,1211821}Whichever you like best.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.07,0:20:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1217076,1219120}Do you know how to shoot it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.12,0:20:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1219120,1220329}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.38,0:20:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1231382,1235678}Let the duel between Victor Langlois\Nand Jules Francoeur begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.55,0:20:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1239557,1242435}Walk forward 10 steps,\Nturn around and shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.22,0:20:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1243227,1244520}One.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.52,0:20:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1244520,1245646}Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.64,0:20:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1245646,1246731}Three.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.73,0:20:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1246731,1247857}Four.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.85,0:20:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1247857,1249025}Five.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.02,0:20:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1249025,1250067}Six.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.06,0:20:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1250067,1251194}Seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.19,0:20:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1251194,1252278}Eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.27,0:20:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1252278,1253362}Nine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.36,0:20:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1253362,1254739}Ten!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.61,0:21:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1300618,1301911}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.91,0:21:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1301911,1303412}Don't do it, I'm begging you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.41,0:21:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1303412,1306082}Victor, if you must shoot,\Nshoot at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.45,0:21:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1308459,1310753}Stay out of this, Geneviève!\NMove out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.75,0:21:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1310753,1311504}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.50,0:21:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1311504,1312672}Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.67,0:21:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1312672,1316175}Geneviève, do you want me\Nto look like a coward?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.17,0:21:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1316175,1316717}Jules!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.71,0:22:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1316717,1320638}Go on, Captain Langlois!\NYou still have your bullet!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.63,0:22:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1320638,1321806}Shoot it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.28,0:22:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1340283,1341617}Jules!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.82,0:22:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1343828,1345997}Jules…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.24,0:22:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1347248,1349125}It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.42,0:22:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1359427,1361887}Be happy, Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.09,0:22:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1363097,1364432}Victor?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.56,0:22:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1368561,1370521}Victor, you…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.73,0:22:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1372732,1375151}I missed my aim.\NThat is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.94,0:23:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1378946,1380614}Will you be all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.99,0:23:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1380990,1384076}This is nothing.\NI would like to be alone for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.32,0:23:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1384327,1386370}I'm sorry, Victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.37,0:23:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1386370,1388873}We'll see each other on\NGovernment of National Defense meeting.
